              <mitigation action="Approve Mitigation" date="2022-02-28 15:02:49 UTC" description="Approved because the projects SetupMockData and SetupEnvironment affected by this flaw are used only during deployment as a one time solution to set up the environments and seed data and the resources are not accessible by anyone after setting up the product." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031kushala.rajanna@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Mitigate by Design" date="2022-02-28 09:11:48 UTC" description="&#13;Technique: M2 :  Establish and maintain control over all of your outputs&#13;&#10;Specifics: Components affected by the vulnerability are ASP.NET Core components in the backend of the application. Specifically, these are dependencies of microsoft packages used in SetupMockData and SetupEnvironment projects. These projects are not hosted in any way, they are only used during deployment process to setup the environments configurations and mock data on lower environments. Therefore we believe these do not pose any security threat as they are not accessible by any attack vector.&#13;&#10;Remaining Risk: No risk&#13;&#10;Verification: Code for SetupMockData and SetupEnvironment projects." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031jakub.spalek@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Reject Mitigation" date="2022-02-28 07:39:37 UTC" description="Rejected because if this is a transitive dependency, try utilizing the https://www.npmjs.com/package/npm-force-resolutions package to force the dependency to a vulnerable free version. Additionally, ensure that only production dependencies are included by running npm install --production and including the generated package-lock.json file in the scan." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031kushala.rajanna@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Mitigate by Design" date="2022-02-25 11:51:37 UTC" description="&#13;Technique: M2 :  Establish and maintain control over all of your outputs&#13;&#10;Specifics: The projects SetupMockData and SetupEnvironment affected by this flaw are used only during deployment as a one time solution to set up the environments and seed data. They are not hosted by any means and therefore are not accessible for any potential attackers.&#13;&#10;Remaining Risk: no risk&#13;&#10;Verification: Check dependencies and purpose for SetupMockData and SetupEnvironment projects in the codebase." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031jakub.spalek@pwc.com"/>
            </mitigations>
