        <vulnerabilities>
          <vulnerability cve_id="SRCCLR-SID-31414" cve_summary="yargs-parser is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS). The `isUnknownOption` function in `yargs-parser.ts` does not properly replace `-` characters from parse, allowing a malicious user to slow down or hang the application when unknown-options-as-args is set to true." cvss_score="5.3" cwe_id="" first_found_date="2023-02-14 10:33:06 UTC" mitigated_date="2021-11-26 08:19:27 UTC" mitigation="true" mitigation_type="Mitigate by Design" severity="3" severity_desc="Medium" vulnerability_affects_policy_compliance="false">
            <mitigations>
              <mitigation action="Approve Mitigation" date="2021-11-26 08:19:27 UTC" description="Approved because the vulnerable method 'isUnknownOption' is not being used by the library, hence satisfies the mitigation by design." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031sayan.basu@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Mitigate by Design" date="2021-11-25 14:36:20 UTC" description="&#13;Technique: M1 :  Establish and maintain control over all of your inputs&#13;&#10;Specifics: We are using @angular/localize package, which uses yargs, which uses yargs-parser. The flaw is in `isUnknownOption` function in `yargs-parser.ts` in package yargs-parser, but the package yargs is not using it, so the flaw does not exists in our scenario.&#10;&#10;Link to the flaw description:&#10;https://sca.analysiscenter.veracode.com/vulnerability-database/security/sca/vulnerability/sid-31414/summary&#10;&#10;and to the repository:&#10;https://github.com/yargs/yargs&#13;&#10;Remaining Risk: none&#13;&#10;Verification: local env" user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031grzegorz.krempa@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Mitigate by Design" date="2021-11-25 08:36:01 UTC" description="&#13;Technique: M1 :  Establish and maintain control over all of your inputs&#13;&#10;Specifics: The package yargs-parser is a dependency of dependencies, that we are using. The dependency tree is looking like this:&#10;&#10;@angular-devkit/build-angular --&gt; used to build angular application, so it is used only locally and in CI&#10;  webpack-dev-server&#10;    yargs&#10;      yargs-parser&#10;&#10;@angular/compiler-cli --&gt; used to build angular application, so it is used only locally and in CI&#10;  yargs&#10;    yargs-parser&#10;&#10;karma --&gt; used to run unit tests locally and in CI&#10;  yargs&#10;    yargs-parser&#10;&#10;protractor --&gt; used to run UI tests locally and in CI&#10;  yargs&#10;    yargs-parser&#10;&#10;stylelint --&gt; used to style the code, so it is used only in local development&#10;  meow&#10;    yargs-parser&#10;&#10;As you can see above, that package is not used in production, so can be safely marked as 'ok'.&#13;&#10;Remaining Risk: none&#13;&#10;Verification: local env" user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031grzegorz.krempa@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Reject Mitigation" date="2021-11-25 07:43:51 UTC" description="Rejected because the proposal is not addressing the flaw. We only do review a production ready code without any build or dev dependencies. If this library is a build dependency and not required in production you can use command 'npm install --prod' to get the production ready version and rescan." user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031sayan.basu@pwc.com"/>
              <mitigation action="Mitigate by Design" date="2021-11-23 12:34:10 UTC" description="&#13;Technique: M1 :  Establish and maintain control over all of your inputs&#13;&#10;Specifics: Package &quot;yargs-parser&quot; in version 20.2.7 is used in 2 packages:&#10;&#10;yargs (16.2.0) is used here:&#10;   @angular/compiler-cli (10.2.5) --&gt; That package is used for compiling and building application - it is not used in production code&#10;meow (9.0.0) is used here:&#10;   stylelint (13.13.0) --&gt; This package is used to prettify files (scss, css), so it is not used in production.&#10;&#10;As you can see that package is not used in production, thus can be safely mitigated.&#13;&#10;Remaining Risk: none&#13;&#10;Verification: local env" user="urn:pwc:pwd:preferredmail:p:2031grzegorz.krempa@pwc.com"/>
            </mitigations>
